ited in our profession.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:200%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Frank Haskew</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">: Once upon a time, you were not allowed to operate, for instance, as a chartered accountant through a company.  That has changed</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> but the rules are still quite difficult to get within, so it is still normal that our members tend to operate through LLPs or partnerships.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:200%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Lord Leigh of Hurley:</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">  Forgive me</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">I am specifically addressing organisations that are not necessarily your members and that are not necessarily accountancy or legal partnerships but that have chosen to become LLPs for reasons that we are trying to understand.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:200%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Charlotte Barbour</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">: </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">It </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">would be quite interesting to take up</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">perhaps </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">in further work with the OTS</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">, the matter of </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">how many relatively recent non-professional LLPs have taken up.  I quite accept that there could be some </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">on the </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">fringes of the low-paid and the highest-paid </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">that</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> have gone into it in order to get the benefits of, say, self-employment.  I appreciate that that is a possibility.  I am not aware of any number work that has been done around that, and it would be helpful to try to quantify that before we bring in these rules, which, from our members’ feedback, seem to have a much wider impact than we would expect to target the evil, if it is there.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:200%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">Q50 </span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The Chairman:</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> Apart from the measures </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">that </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">we have been discussing, the draft </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">B</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">ill also includes proposals affecting alternative investment fund managers and countering the practice of reducing tax liabilities by transferring assets or income streams within a partnership.  None of your written submissions h